        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1881-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1881-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="556" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <head>No. 552.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Christiancy</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1881-05-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 9,
                            1881</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 143.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In your last dispatch, No.—, you informed this
                        Department that the Chilian Government refused absolutely to recognize
                        General Piérola as representing the civil authority in Peru, and that Señor
                        Calderon was at the head of a provisional government.</p>
                <p>If the Calderon government is supported by the character and intelligence of
                        Peru and is really endeavoring to restore constitutional government with a
                        view both to order within and negotiation with Chili for peace, you may
                        recognize it as the existing provisional government, and render what aid you
                        can by advice and good offices to that end.</p>
                <p>Mr. Elmore has been received by me as the confidential agent of such
                        provisional government.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>JAMES G. BLAINE.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
